   <head>On Mr. ****, Schoolmaster at ***.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">BEHOLD the lordly pedant in his school,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">How stern his brow, how absolute his rule!</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The trembling boys start at his aweful nod;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Jove's sceptre is less dreaded than his rod.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">See him at home before the sovereign dame!</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">How fawning, how obsequious, and how tame!</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Prosper, bright amazon, to thee 'tis given,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Like Juno, to rule him who rules the heaven.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
